    "recap_headline": "Northwestern University Athletics",
    "recap_text": "EUGENE, Ore. \u2013\nNorthwestern fell to No. 21 Oregon, 20-6, in the series opener on Friday night at PK Park.\nNo. 21 Oregon (18-3, 6-1 Big Ten) took a commanding lead early with 10 runs on eight hits in the bottom of the first.\nINF\nNoah Ruiz\nslugged his third homer of the season, a solo shot to right field in the top of the second to put Northwestern (7-10-1, 1-3 Big Ten) on the scoreboard. Ruiz's homer gave him his team-high 16th RBI of the season.\nThe Ducks continued to add on with three in the third, two in the fourth, one in the fifth and four in the sixth.\nIn the top of the seventh, INF\nOwen McElfatrick\nmashed his third homer of the season, a three-run home run to left-center field. The homer, the 27th of McElfatrick's career, moved the Tampa, Fla., native into a tie for fifth place in program history with Joe Hietpas (1998-01, 27).\nNorthwestern added two more runs in the seventh. OF\nCarter Danz\nnotched his first career RBI, scoring OF\nMarty Kaplan\nwith a sacrifice fly and INF\nRyan Kucherak\nscored on a wild pitch.\nRHP Will Sanford (4-0) worked 5.0 one-run innings for the Ducks, allowing one hit and three walks, striking out eight.\nGame two of the weekend series is slated for 4:05 p.m. CT on Saturday afternoon. RHP\nGarrett Shearer\nis scheduled to make the start for the Wildcats, and RHP Collin Clarke set to toe the rubber for the Ducks.",
